  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A literature-review activity was conducted to survey published hemolysis correlations and benchmark datasets, and the results are presented as the primary validation evidence. The review synthesised findings from seven peer-reviewed sources covering power-law hemolysis models and confirmed that the chosen model parameters fall within reported ranges. This evidence is treated as sufficient to satisfy the validation requirement for the hemolysis QoI.",
